Class DataMatrix

java.lang.Object
DataMatrix
All Implemented Interfaces:
BarcodeIO
class DataMatrix
extends java.lang.Object
implements BarcodeIO
Scans and processes an array of boolean values representing a barcode with limit lines on all sides. Can translate this barcode to text or text into a barcode.
Author:
rshum

    • generateImageFromText

      public boolean generateImageFromText()
      Clears values from image array and translates private text member to barcode image (stored in private image array). The barcode is generated in the "upper left" portion of the array first and then pulled to the "bottom left".
      Specified by:
      generateImageFromText in interface BarcodeIO
      Returns:
      TRUE if successful and FALSE if not

    • translateImageToText

      public boolean translateImageToText()

      Specified by:
      translateImageToText in interface BarcodeIO
      Returns:
      TRUE if successful and FALSE if not

    • readCharFromCol

      private char readCharFromCol​(int col)
      Translates binary values of the barcode at paramter col into a char value, ignoring upper and lower limit lines. Should not be called on the left and right limit lines. Also translates extended ASCII values.
      Parameters:
      col - column on private member image array to be translated
      Returns:
      char value of translated column

    • writeCharToCol

      private boolean writeCharToCol​(int col, int code)
      Assigns boolean values to the parameter "col" of the array contained in the private member "image". Also writes the top and bottom borders. Array should be initialized (all elements set to false). Writes column to upper left hand corner of the array.
      Parameters:
      col - column of array that should be written
      code - ASCII value of character to be written
      Returns:
      FALSE if column cannot be written, TRUE after writing

    • writeColumnBorders

      private boolean writeColumnBorders​(int col)
      Writes top and bottom borders for parameter column in image array.
      Parameters:
      col - column who's borders should be written
      Returns:
      FALSE if borders cannot be written, TRUE otherwise

    • writeLeftBorder

      private boolean writeLeftBorder()
      Draws left border of image array on upper left hand corner.
      Returns:
      FALSE if border cannot be written, TRUE otherwise

    • writeRightBorder

      private boolean writeRightBorder​(int col)
      Draws right border on the top of the array, at the parameter "col".
      Parameters:
      col - column that should contain the right limit line
      Returns:
      FALSE if border cannot be written, TRUE after writing

    • cleanImage

      private void cleanImage()
      Identifies lower left hand corner of the barcode and shifts it to the bottom left corner of the array.

    • computeSignalWidth

      private int computeSignalWidth()
      Determines the width of the barcode image (excludes white space in the array). Calculated from left to right limit lines. Should be run after image is pulled to the lower left corner.
      Returns:
      the width of the barcode, including limit lines

    • computeSignalHeight

      private int computeSignalHeight()
      Determines the height of the barcode image (excludes white space in the array). Calculated from lower to top limit lines, using the left most limit line. Leftmost limit line is a solid block of TRUE values until height is reached. Should be run after image is pulled to the lower left corner.
      Returns:
      the height of the barcode, including limit lines
